00024 /* Timeout guard interval. This value is the basic
00025  * timeout applied by the api side whenever it calls
00026  * icapi_rcv(). It is added to the application's
00027  * specified timeout on API calls, while the caller's
00028  * timeout is used directly by the SDK when it is
00029  * awaiting a response from the modem.  This ensure that
00030  * the modem * timeout will always happen first. If the
00031  * icapi_rcv() * times out, then this is some kind of
00032  * system failure, * like the SDK process has died.
00033  */
00034 #define AMTIMEGUARD 1000

00144 /*************
00145  *
00146  * Name:    amipccb
00147  *
00148  * Purpose: AM IPC Task control block structure
00149  *
00150  * Members:
00151  *          amdlcb     - DL package control block for logging
00152  *          amicmsgque - AMIPC task's event queue for requests
00153  *          amevtpool  - MM pool for events coming in from hosts.
00154  *          amipcwaiter- Waiter structure for blocking AM IPC task until a
00155  *                       response is sent to the host(s).
00156  *          amnotifpool - MM pool blocks for our Notification queue.This is
00157  *                        guaranteed to be enough for the total number of
00158  *                        notifications defined on the API side.
00159  *          amnotifheadq- Notification queue head
00160  *          ameventheadq- Event queue head of local queue (off of SMT queue)
00161  *          amreqbusy   - Busy flag for when response has not been sent
00162  *          amipcshell  - Array of DS shell info needed for starting IPC shells
00163  *                        (thread creation needs storage space, can't use stack)
00164  *
00165  * Notes:   The AM IPC task runs on the SDK side only.
00166  *          Incoming messages are buffered by the DS task which we eventually
00167  *          release after sending the message.
00168  *          Note that IPC for Request/Response traffic is handled by DS. We only
00169  *          need to initialize DS shell using IC defines.
00170  *
00171  **************/
00172 struct amipccb
00173 {
00174     struct dlusercb     amdlcb;
00175     struct icsmtcb      amicmsgque;
00176     struct mmpool       amevtpool;
00177     struct swi_oswaiter amipcwaiter;
00178 #if 0 
00179     struct mmpool       amnotifpool;
00180     struct amipcnotifq  amnotifheadq;
00181 #endif
00182     struct qllink       ameventheadq;
00183     swi_bool            amreqbusy;
00184     struct dsipcshell   amipcsh[CIMAXRRPAIR];
00185 };
